(1) There is established a body corporate known as the Fair Work Agency.

(2) The functions of the Fair Work Agency are—
(a) to enforce compliance with the National Minimum Wage Act 1998, Working Time Regulations 1998, holiday pay obligations, the Gangmasters (Licensing) Act 2004, and the Employment Agencies Act 1973;
(b) to investigate labour market abuses;
(c) to provide information and guidance to workers and employers;
(d) to bring proceedings before employment tribunals on behalf of workers who lack the means or ability to bring proceedings themselves.
